ns2:PrimaryTypeDefinition.ns1:desc: This MO represents a Cell and contains parameters needed by the cell. It also contains parameters for the mandatory common channels.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Obsolete attribute for test purpose.
Obsolete attribute for test purpose.
Obsolete attribute for test purpose.
Obsolete attribute for test purpose.
Obsolete attribute for test purpose.

The reported rank distribution indicates the rank of UEs that are in an Open and Closed Loop Spatial Multiplexing mode, where rank is reported.
PDF ranges: [0]: Rank = 1 [1]: Rank = 2 [2]: Rank = 3 [3]: Rank = 4

The total number of successful RLC PDU transmissions (ACKs) in the downlink direction.
When carrier aggregation is used, the total number of successful RLC PDU transmissions (ACKs) in the downlink direction is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

The total number of unsuccessful RLC PDU and RLC PDU segment transmissions (NACKs) in the downlink direction.
When carrier aggregation is used, the total number of unsuccessful RLC PDU and RLC PDU segment transmissions (NACKs) in the downlink direction is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

The effective DL transport time comprises those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer. This counts for carrier aggregation and non-carrier aggregation UEs. Used for PDCP timebase.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The effective DL transport time, comprising those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer, is registered on PCell.

The total volume of compressed PDCP SDU headers that has been transmitted from the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume of compressed PDCP SDU headers that has been transmitted from the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied is measured on PCell.

The total DL PDCP SDU volume per QCI that is transmitted in the last TTI when the buffer for a DRB that maps to the given QCI is emptied.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total DL PDCP SDU volume per QCI that is transmitted in the last TTI when the buffer for a DRB that maps to the given QCI is emptied is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

The total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on Data Radio Bearers in the downlink direction per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on Data Radio Bearers in the downlink direction per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN0.
PLMN0 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId located on ENodeBFunction.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN0 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN1.
PLMN1 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[0] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN1 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN2.
PLMN2 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[1] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN2 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN3.
PLMN3 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[2] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN3 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN4.
PLMN4 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[3] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN4 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN5.
PLMN5 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[4] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN5 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN6.
PLMN6 refers to an unexpected PLMN, that is, a PLMN that cannot be associated with any PLMN configured in the ENodeBFunction or cell.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN6 is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

The total volume of uncompressed PDCP SDU headers that has been received in the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume of uncompressed PDCP SDU headers that has been received in the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

The total number of bits (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction.
SRB0 volume is not included in this counter.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total number of bits (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction is measured on PCell.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer is measured on PCell.

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) successfully transmitted (RLC acknowledged by UE) in the downlink.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) successfully transmitted (RLC acknowledged by UE) in the downlink is measured on PCell.

Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) transmitted successfully per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) transmitted successfully per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received by RBS in PDCP in the downlink.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received by RBS in PDCP in the downlink is measured on PCell.

Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) received in PDCP in the RBS per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) received in PDCP in the RBS per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to Active Queue Management (AQM).
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to AQM is measured on PCell.

Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI discarded due to Active Queue Management (AQM).
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI discarded due to AQM is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

Number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in downlink due to handover and reestablishment procedures, including procedures for EN-DC setup.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in the downlink due to handover and reestablishment procedures is measured on PCell.

Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to HO per QCI, including HO during EN-DC setup procedure.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to HO per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) for which no part has been transmitted over the air in the downlink that are discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management is measured on PCell.

Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI that are discarded in the PDCP layer due to reasons other than handover or active queue management. No part of these packets has been transmitted over the air.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air in the downlink direction but not positively acknowledged, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, due to reasons other than handover. Only applicable to DRB packets.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air in the downlink direction but not positively acknowledged, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, due to reasons other than handover, is measured on PCell.

Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air but not positively acknowledged due to reasons other than handover, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air but not positively acknowledged due to reasons other than handover, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

Aggregated DL Latency for a measurement period. The effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering the buffer until the first data has been transmitted to the UE.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

Aggregated DL Latency when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

Aggregated DL Latency for a measurement period per QCI. When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).
Compressed: True

Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

Number of samples for DL Latency measurements during measurement period per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).
Compressed: True

Minimum cell DL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) is measured on PCell.

Peak cell DL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) is measured on PCell.

The DL transmission time used for DL DRB Throughput per QCI. It comprises of time periods from when the first piece of data in a data burst is transmitted until the second last piece of data in the data burst is transmitted.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL transmission time used for DL DRB Throughput per QCI is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).
Compressed: True
The value component of the RDN.

The channel number for the central downlink frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified EUTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. The values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation as well as on the supported frequency bands in the RBS. Note: Use the MO action changeFrequency if the DL frequency must be changed after the cell is initially setup.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and set together with earfcnul. The earfcnul and earfcndl values are dependent and relate according to default EUTRA TX channel to RX channel separation as specified in 3GPP TS 36.101 for the EUTRA operating band and channel bandwidth of the cell.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Channel number for the central UL frequency. The mapping from channel number to physical frequency for specified EUTRA bands is described in 3GPP TS 36.104. Values that can be used depend on national, operator-specific frequency allocation, as well as on the supported frequency bands of the RBS. Value 0 means that the UL channel number is N/A for the DL-only bands.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and set together with earfcndl. The earfcnul and earfcndl values are dependent and relate according to default EUTRA TX channel to RX channel separation as specified in 3GPP TS 36.101 for the EUTRA operating band and channel bandwidth of the cell.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For 1.4 MHz system bandwidth the recommended value is 50.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of Scheduling Request (SR) resources available on the PUCCH channel. For 1.4 MHz system bandwidth the recommended value is 50.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Cell runs new set-up procedure. All cell-connected UEs are released and connected again.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
The downlink channel bandwidth in the cell.
Valid values: 1400, 3000, 5000, 10000, 15000, 20000
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and shall be set to the same as ulChannelBandwidth.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
The uplink channel bandwidth in the cell.
Valid values: 1400, 3000, 5000, 10000, 15000, 20000
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This attribute is dependent on and shall be set to the same as dlChannelBandwidth.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Defines the maximum distance from the base station where a connection to a UE can be setup and/or maintained.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Common SR periodicity, used for all UEs.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: For 1.4 MHz: Only valid inputs are 10 and 20.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Defines the Transmission Mode (e.g. Transmit Diversity and Closed-Loop Spatial Multiplexing) that shall be used for the UEs that are connected to the cell. See 3GPP TS 36.213 table 7.1-5 for a definition of Transmission Mode.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: If mbsfnSubframesForTm9 enabled, TM9-capable UEs are reconfigured to TM9.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
The transmission mode and rank distributions provide more detailed information on the extent to which each transmission mode and rank is used.
PDF ranges: [0]: Transmit diversity [1]: Open Loop SM Rank 1 [2]: Open Loop SM Rank 2 [3]: Closed Loop SM rank 1 [4]: Closed Loop SM rank 2 [5]: Reserved [6]: Reserved [7]: Reserved [8]: Closed Loop SM rank 3 [9]: Closed Loop SM rank 4 [10]: Multiple Layer Transmission rank 1 [11]: Multiple Layer Transmission rank 2 [12]: Open Loop SM rank 3 [13]: Open Loop SM rank 4 [14]: Multiple Layer Transmission rank 3 [15]: Multiple Layer Transmission rank 4
Sum of all sample values recorded for number of UEs using TTI Bundling.
Counts the number of times the corresponding pmTtiBundlingUeSum has accumulated a new sample.
Maximum sample value of number of UEs using TTI Bundling.
Indicates if the cell is operated with downlink only and with no uplink.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Must be false if catm1SupportEnabled is true.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to the target cell being a downlink-only cell (EUtranCellFDD.isDlOnly = TRUE)

The number of channel selection PUCCH resource sets (CS sets) to reserve in each cell for secondary cell HARQ feedback. To conserve PUCCH resource, this attribute can be set to 0 if the cell is not used as PCell for Carrier Aggregation.

Determines the number of Channel Selection (CS) PUCCH resources in a CS set.
Set to 1 when all SCell candidates are configured with transmission mode 1 or 2. Set to 2 when at least one SCell candidate is configured with transmission mode 3 or higher.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies:
Applicable only when attribute noOfChannelSelectionSets > 0.
Only SCell candidates with TM mode resource requirements that match the CS set size are considered for carrier aggregation.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: This attribute specifies configuration type of CSI-RS (Channel State Information Reference Signal) for FDD 8Tx.

The path loss distribution of the Radio Link Control (RLC) Service Data Units (SDU), that are received for a VoIP bearer in uplink.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of samples =< 115 dB [1]: Number of samples in range ]115..116] dB [2]: Number of samples in range ]116..117] dB ... [37]: Number of samples in range ]151..152] dB [38]: Number of samples in range ]152..153] dB [39]: Number of samples > 153 dB

The path loss distribution of the Radio Link Control (RLC) Service Data Units (SDU), that are estimated in RLC to be lost for a VoIP bearer in uplink.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of samples =< 115 dB [1]: Number of samples in range ]115..116] dB [2]: Number of samples in range ]116..117] dB ... [37]: Number of samples in range ]151..152] dB [38]: Number of samples in range ]152..153] dB [39]: Number of samples > 153 dB

Downlink carrier aggregation capability reported by UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Only the maximum number of SCells, where at least one of the carriers is TDD, is considered.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus one TDD SCell. [1]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus two SCells, with at least one TDD SCell. [2]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus three SCells, with at least one TDD SCell. [3]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus four SCells, with at least one TDD SCell.

Number of configured downlink SCells identified by duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Only one bin is pegged for each UE and sample, based on all configured SCells when the counter is updated. For example, for a UE configured with one FDD and one TDD SCell, only bin 8 is incremented and not bin 0 or bin 4.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD SCell. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two FDD SCells. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three FDD SCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with four FDD SCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one TDD SCell. [5]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two TDD SCells. [6]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three TDD SCells. [7]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with four TDD SCells. [8]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD and one TDD SCell. [9]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD and two TDD SCells. [10]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD and three TDD SCells. [11]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two FDD and one TDD SCell. [12]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two FDD and two TDD SCells. [13]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three FDD and one TDD SCell.

Number of activated downlink SCells, identified by duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated FDD SCell. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated FDD SCells. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated FDD SCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated FDD SCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated TDD SCell. [5]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated TDD SCells. [6]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated TDD SCells. [7]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated TDD SCells. [8]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one FDD and one TDD SCells activated. [9]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one FDD and two TDD SCells activated. [10]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one FDD and three TDD SCells activated. [11]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two FDD and one TDD SCells activated. [12]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two FDD and two TDD SCells activated. [13]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three FDD and one TDD SCells activated.
Maximum number of neighbor cells whose CRS Assistance Information is sent to UE.
Number of UEs that are capable of CRS-IC.
Number of CRS-IC-capable UE measurement samples.

Internal DL channel bandwidth in the cell with reduced channel bandwidth. Reduced bandwidth for an LTE carrier creates free space for carriers of other radio technologies to use within a standard spectrum 5 MHz or 10 MHz. Other spectrum will generate the undefined value 0. Reduced channel bandwidth is only supported on some radios.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Value must be the same as ulInternalChannelBandwidth value. dlInternalChannelBandwidth values 4200, 4400, 4600 and 4800 are only allowed when dlChannelBandwidth is 5000. dlInternalChannelBandwidth value 9000 is only allowed when dlChannelBandwidth is 10000.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Internal UL channel bandwidth in the cell with reduced channel bandwidth. Reduced bandwidth for an LTE carrier creates free space for carriers of other radio technologies to use within a standard spectrum 5 MHz or 10 MHz. Other spectrum will generate the undefined value 0. Reduced channel bandwidth is only supported on some radios.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Value must be the same dlInternalChannelBandwidth value. ulInternalChannelBandwidth values 4200, 4400, 4600 and 4800 are only allowed when ulChannelBandwidth is 5000. ulInternalChannelBandwidth value 9000 is only allowed when ulChannelBandwidth is 10000.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
For Inter-eNodeB (IeNB) or Elastic RAN carrier aggregation interactions, records mean number of UEs that activate DL External SCell (ESCell). Counted by number of component carriers hosted on external eNodeBs and simultaneously activated. UE activates DL ESCell for carrier aggregation if eNodeB sends a MACCE activation on PCell PDSCH that is ACKED by UE. PDF ranges indicate the number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have simultaneously activated ESCells equal to the PDF range number.
PDF ranges: [0]: UEs that have zero activated ESCell. Includes UE having this cell as PCell with at least one configured DL SCell or ESCell. [1]: UEs that have one simultaneously activated ESCell. [2]: UEs that have two simultaneously activated ESCells. [3]: UEs that have three simultaneously activated ESCells. [4]: UEs that have four simultaneously activated ESCells.

For Inter-eNodeB (IeNB) or Elastic RAN carrier aggregation interactions, records number of configured DL External SCells (ESCells) of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as PCell. PDF ranges indicate the number of carrier-aggregation capable UEs that are configured with ESCells equal to the PDF range number.
PDF ranges: [0]: UEs that are not configured with any ESCell. Includes all carrier aggregation-capable UEs using this cell as PCell with no SCell configured or at least one SCell configured. [1]: UEs that are configured with one ESCell. [2]: UEs that are configured with two ESCells. [3]: UEs that are configured with three ESCells. [4]: UEs that are configured with four ESCells.

For Inter-eNodeB (IeNB) or Elastic RAN carrier aggregation interactions, records mean number of UEs that have data scheduled on a DL External SCell (ESCell). Counted by number of component carriers hosted on external eNodeBs and scheduled simultaneously. UE is scheduled for carrier aggregation if eNodeB sends a PDCCH assignment indicating a PDSCH assignment. PDF ranges indicate the number of carrier aggregation-activated UEs that have simultaneously scheduled ESCells equal to the PDF range number.
PDF ranges: [0]: UEs that have zero scheduled ESCell. Includes scheduling only on PCell or SCells. [1]: UEs that have one simultaneously scheduled ESCell. [2]: UEs that have two simultaneously scheduled ESCells. [3]: UEs that have three simultaneously scheduled ESCells. [4]: UEs that have four simultaneously scheduled ESCells.
Total of successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for SCell traffic as measured and reported on the PCell.
Total of successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for external SCell (ESCell) traffic as measured and reported on the PCell.
Total of assumed successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for external SCell (ESCell) traffic as measured and reported on the ESCell.
SINR threshold for triggering a switch to TTI bundling.
Hysteresis of SINR threshold for triggering a switch to TTI bundling.
Controls if UE remains in TTI bundling mode after handover.
Controls if UE remains in TTI bundling mode after reestablishment.
Number of PUCCH Format 3 PRB pairs.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when 3CC Carrier aggregation Extension Feature (FAJ 121 3084) is enabled.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Upper limit of valid subframes for DL transmission of BR traffic.

Enables dynamic switching between TM9 and TM4.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if radio equipment supports AAS functionality.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Enables PDSCH transmissions to UEs in Transmission Mode 9, and defines subframes within a frame configured as MBSFN subframe for this.
Enabling causes TM9-capable UEs to be reconfigured to TM9. Performance of these UEs improves due to reduced inter-cell interference from cell-specific reference signals. UEs not supporting TM9 cannot be scheduled in MBSFN subframes, leading to worse performance. CSI-RS is transmitted when feature is enabled.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if the licenses for CRS Interference Reduction for TM9 using MBSFN Subframes, and Dual-Antenna Downlink Performance Package are activated. For four transmit antenna systems, also the license for 4x2 Quad Antenna Downlink Performance Package must be activated. Feature will not take effect when enabled together with feature LTE Broadcast.

Controls allocation of PRACH to upper or lower part of band.
Controls both LTE PRACH and PRACH for Bandwidth Reduced (BR) UEs together. For example, it can be used for avoiding interfered part of band. 0: Allocate PRACH from lower part of band. 1: Allocate PRACH from upper part of band.

Controls allocation of PUSCH for BR UEs to upper or lower part of band.
Controls PUSCH from BR UEs, except msg3. For example, it can be used for the following: - To avoid interfered part of band. - To be used in combination with Flexible Channel Bandwidth. 0: Allocate PUSCH from BR UEs, except msg3, to lower part of band. 1: Allocate PUSCH from BR UEs, except msg3, to upper part of band.

Controls allocation of msg3 for BR UEs to upper or lower part of band.
Controls msg3 from BR UEs. For example, it can be used for the following: - To avoid interfered part of band. - To be used in combination with Flexible Channel Bandwidth. 0: Allocate msg3 from BR UEs to lower part of band. 1: Allocate msg3 from BR UEs to upper part of band.

PrimaryTypeAttribute: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnb Description
The total number of abnormal UE Contexts Releases initiated by the RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically or by manual intervention) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: There is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

The total number of UE Context Releases initiated by the MME excluding successful handover. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
The total number of UE Context Releases initiated by the MME excluding successful handover and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of normal UE Context Releases triggered by RBS. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

The UL volume transfer time used for UL UE Throughput. It comprises of time periods from when the 5th MAC SDU data reception of an UL buffer transfer on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer.

The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs available for transmission in the downlink.
The value of the counter depends on the FDD/TDD configuration and in TDD also the special subframe configuration.

The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs available for transmission in the uplink.
The value of the counter depends on the FDD/TDD configuration.
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Signaling Radio Bearers (SRB) in the uplink.
Aggregated number of attempts to allocate PUCCH resources.
The number of times a PUCCH allocation request for CQI resource(s) could not be granted
The number of times a PUCCH allocation request for SR resource(s) could not be granted.
The number of allocated CFRA preambles.
The number of detected contention-based random access preambles from non-bandwidth-reduced UEs.
The number of detected contention-free (explicitly signaled) random access preambles.

Number of transport blocks on MAC level scheduled in UL where UE is considered to be power-limited. Transport blocks are excluded if scheduled for UEs with activated secondary carrier that is configured for UL transmissions.

Number of transport blocks on MAC level scheduled in UL where UE is not considered to be power-limited. Transport blocks are excluded if scheduled for UEs with activated secondary carrier that is configured for UL transmissions.
The total amount of physical resources used for transmission in the downlink. Both successful and unsuccessful transmissions are counted.
The total amount of physical resources used for transmission in the uplink. Both successful and unsuccessful transmissions are counted.
Successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the downlink. This counter includes possible padding bits. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

Successfully transferred data volume on MAC-level in UL. This counter includes possible padding bits. Accumulates data traffic for UEs that use this cell as their PCell or SCell. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

Reported CQI value from UEs not in higher order modulation (HOM) mode in a distribution. Bandwidth reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.
PDF ranges: [0]: CQI = 0 [1]: CQI = 1 [2]: CQI = 2 [3]: CQI = 3 [4]: CQI = 4 [5]: CQI = 5 [6]: CQI = 6 [7]: CQI = 7 [8]: CQI = 8 [9]: CQI = 9 [10]: CQI = 10 [11]: CQI = 11 [12]: CQI = 12 [13]: CQI = 13 [14]: CQI = 14 [15]: CQI = 15
Number of CBRA preambles for which no random access response (RA Msg2) was sent due to expiration of the random access response window. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.
The number of CFRA preambles for which no random access response (RA Msg2) was sent due to expiration of the random access response window.
The number of successfully detected RA Msg3 for CBRA from non-bandwidth-reduced UEs.
The number of successfully completed CFRA procedures. Measured when first UL-SCH message is received after detection of the CFRA preamble.
The total number of successful RLC PDU transmissions (ACKs) in the uplink direction.
The total number of unsuccessful RLC PDU and RLC PDU segment transmissions (NACKs) in the uplink direction.
The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts.
The total number of failed RRC Connection Establishments due to lack of connected users license.
The total number of successful RRC Connection Establishments.
Number of UEs considered active in the downlink direction. For a carrier aggregation UE, is counted on PCell.
Number of UEs considered active in the uplink direction.
Number of neighbour relations added by the ANR function.
Number of neighbour relations removed by the ANR function.
The total number of traffic Bad Coverage measurement reports received.
The total number of traffic Best Cell measurement reports received.
Length of time the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled). The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

Length of time the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily. The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.
The total number of added E-RAB Establishment attempts. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
The total number of initial E-RAB Establishment attempts. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.
The total number of failed establishment of added E-RABs due to license rejects (Multiple Radio Bearer per user or RLC UM). Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

The total number of failed establishment of initial E-RABs due to license rejects (Multiple Radio Bearer per user or RLC UM). Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.
The total number of successfully added E-RABs. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
The total number of successful initial E-RAB Establishments. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.
Counts the number of times the corresponding Sum counters has been incremented. Associated ACC pmCounter pmErabLevSum.
Sum of all sample values recorded for Number of simultaneous E-RABs
The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases triggered by eNB per cell.
The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the eNB and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically or by manual intervention) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of abnormal ERAB releases per cell by the eNB due to handover execution failure and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of abnormal ERAB releases by the eNB per cell due to handover preparation and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell due to S1 Interface Down, X2 Interface Down, or Transport Resource Unavailable. Preconditions are that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed and there is data in the UL or DL buffer.

The total number of abnormal ERAB releases by the eNB per cell due that the contact with the UE is lost with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the MME excluding successful handover. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
The total number of E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME (per cell) and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of normal E-RAB Releases triggered by eNB per cell.
The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to license for connected users being exceeded.
The number of Incoming Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to lack of license for handover.

Counts the number of S1AP Paging messages discarded and not broadcasted in this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagReceived. Both non-prioritized, prioritized S1AP Paging messages and eDRX pagings are included.
Counts the number of S1AP Paging messages routed to this cell. Both non-prioritized, prioritized S1AP Paging and eDRX paging messages are included.
Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) lost in the uplink.
Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received in the uplink.
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction and transmitted over the GTP-U.

The total number of bits (PDCP SDU) on Signaling Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the RBS) in the uplink direction.
SRB0 volume is not included in this counter.
The availability status. It contains details about operationalState. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.
The operational state. This attribute is set by the application in the RBS.
The administrative state.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute to LOCKED or SHUTTINGDOWN causes loss of traffic. Changing this attribute can cause all unlocked NBIoT cells to change administrativeState to LOCKED and then UNLOCKED. This happens when one of the following thresholds is crossed: 18 EUTRAN cells + 1 NBIoT cell or 9 NBIoT cells.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
RBS internal ID attribute for EUtranCell. Must be unique in the RBS. Together with the Node ID and Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) this is a universally unique cell ID.
Range 0-255.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Physical layer cell ID group.
Physical layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical layer cell ID groups. Each group contains 3 unique subidentities. Used with physicalLayerSubCellId to calculate physical layer cell ID.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Subidentity within the physical layer cell ID group.
Physical layer cell IDs are grouped into 168 unique physical layer cell ID groups. Each group contains 3 unique subidentities. Used with physicalLayerCellIdGroup to calculate physical layer cell ID.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Label for free use.
Tracking Area Code for the EUtran Cell.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Indicates if the DRX function in the cell is activated.
Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1.
Intended type of CDMA2000 system time to broadcast in SIB8, if applicable.
The actual type of CDMA2000 system time that is broadcast in SIB8.

Number of resource blocks outside each Physical Uplink Control Channel (PUCCH) region that are available for scheduling Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
Note: Both the value of this attribute and the amount of resources allocated for PUCCH impacts where the resource allocation of the PRACH starts.
The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a QPSK modulation.
The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a QPSK modulation.
The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a QPSK modulation.
The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a QPSK modulation.
The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 16QAM modulation.
The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a 16QAM modulation.
The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 16QAM modulation.
The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a 16QAM modulation.
The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 64QAM modulation.
The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 64QAM modulation.
Aggregated time for the downlink MAC delay measure. The time for each sample shall show the time between reception from RLC until it is successfully received in the UE or HARQ failure occurs.
Number of samples for RLC delay measurements.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 19.Q1. Replaced by pmRlcDelayTimeDl2. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Aggregated time for the downlink RLC delay measure.
Peak number of UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode, excluding bandwidth-reduced UEs.
Sum of all sample values recorded for "number of UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode", excluding bandwidth-reduced UEs.
Number of times the corresponding Sum counter has accumulated a new sample. Associated ACC pmCounter pmRrcConnLevSum.
The offset applied to the signaled Qrxlevmin. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevminoffset in 3GPP TS 36.304. Value 1000 means it is not sent and the UE sets Qrxlevminoffset=0dB.
The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to E-Utra.
The total number of occasions when a downlink HARQ feedback for a transport block using QPSK modulation was not received from an UE and DTX is considered the reason.
The total number of occasions when a downlink HARQ feedback for a transport block using 16QAM modulation was not received from an UE and DTX is considered the reason.
The total number of occasions when a downlink HARQ feedback for a transport block using 64QAM modulation was not received from an UE and DTX is considered the reason.

The total number of occasions when an uplink grant was meant for HARQ transmission of a transport block using QPSK modulation in the uplink direction, where DTX is considered the reason for no reception of HARQ in uplink in the eNB.

The total number of occasions when an uplink grant was meant for HARQ transmission of a transport block using 16QAM modulation in the uplink direction, where DTX is considered the reason for no reception of HARQ in uplink in the eNB.
The total number of normal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the eNB and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of normal UE Context Releases triggered by RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for paging.
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for System Information.
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Data Radio Bearers (DRB) in the uplink.
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Data Radio Bearers (DRB) in the downlink.

Indicates if the feature OTDOA Support in SUPL Environment is ACTIVATED or DEACTIVATED in the cell.

The Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) index value for the cell defines the periodicity of the PRS occasions and the PRS subframe offset, as defined in 3GPP TS 36.211. The value -1 (default) means that this parameter will not be used for setting the PRS period and prsSubframeOffset. Instead the parameter prsPeriod shall be used to directly set the PRS period while prsSubframeOffset will be set by the system to guarantee non collision with SIB1.
The number of consecutive downlink sub-frames with positioning reference signals as defined in 3GPP TS 36.211. Values define 1, 2, 4, or 6 consecutive sub-frames.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: None

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The degree of latitude of the transmitter antenna position. In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell): For indoor system, antenna of any sector. For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.
The degree of longitude of the transmitter antenna position. In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell): For indoor system, antenna of any sector. For outdoor system,antenna of macro sector.

Transmitter antenna altitude (meters). Use +/- values to denote height/depth. In case of Combined Cell (multi-sector cell): For indoor system, antenna of any sector. For outdoor system, antenna of macro sector.

Semi-major axis of uncertainty. The uncertainty (r) is derived from the uncertainty code (k) by:
r = 10 * ((1.1^k) - 1).

Semi-minor axis of uncertainty. The uncertainty (r) is derived from the uncertainty code (k) by:
r = 10 * ((1.1^k) - 1).

Orientation of the major axis of uncertainty, in degrees clockwise from north. Orientation value (N) is derived by the formula:
N <= X < (N + 1)
where X is the orientation in degrees (0 - 180).
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: None

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The uncertainty altitude (h) expressed in meters is derived from the uncertainty altitude (k) by h = 45*((1.025)^k - 1).
Percentage of confidence that the target device is within the ellipsoid defined by the three axes of uncertainty: semi-major, semi-minor, and altitude.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: None

The decimal part of the GPS time for the most recent occurrence of System Frame Number (SFN)=0 in the cell.
Unit: 2^(-32) second
Indicates if the primary PLMN ID in the cell is reserved for operator use. The primary PLMN ID is reserved if this attribute is set to true.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can block traffic in the cell.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: the attribute eNodeBPlmnId in the parent ENodeBFunction will hold the value of the primary PLMN ID.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: For the list of PLMN IDs in the cell, indicates if they are reserved for operator use. The list must have the same number of entries as additonalPlmnList. The PLMN ID appearing in additionalPlmnList[x] is reserved when additionalPlmnListReserved[x] is set to true.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: The length of this list must be the same as the list in addtionalPlmnList.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Lists additional PLMN IDs supported in cell.
List can include up to five PLMNs that must be same in all EUtranCells in same Tracking Area (TA). If not set at MO creation, then attribute is automatically set to a list of five elements, each representing a dummy PLMN identity.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Lists the PLMN IDs served by at least one MME. The PLMN ID is defined in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId in the parent ENodeBFunction. PLMN IDs from additionalPlmnList also appear in this list. The list may include up to 6 PLMNs.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN0.
PLMN0 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId located on ENodeBFunction.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN1.
PLMN1 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[0] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN2.
PLMN2 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[1] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN3.
PLMN3 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[2] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN4.
PLMN4 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[3] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN5.
PLMN5 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[4] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN6.
PLMN6 refers to an unexpected PLMN, that is, a PLMN that cannot be associated with any PLMN configured in the ENodeBFunction or cell.

The number of times the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled).

The number of times the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - a reconfiguration of an Unlocked cell that required the cell to be temporarily disabled.

The number of times the cell has been enabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Unlocked by the operator or - a reconfiguration of an Unlocked cell that required the cell to be temporarily disabled was successfully completed.

The number of non-admitted E-RABs at an incoming handover preparation procedure, due to license for Multiple E-RAB being exceeded.

Peak number of UEs considered active in the downlink direction, i.e. has designated data in UE dedicated buffer in the eNB. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

Peak number of UEs considered active in the uplink direction, i.e. the UE is considered to have data in its buffer. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

Peak cell UL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been received in the uplink direction, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.

Minimum cell UL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been received in the uplink direction, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.

Distribution of the DL UE throughput. One DL UE throughput sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers per UE, that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction, with a time interval applicable to the volume measurement. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.
PDF ranges: [0]: 0 < UL UE thp sample < 1.000 [1]: 1.000 <= UL UE thp sample < 3.000 [2]: 3.000 <= UL UE thp sample < 5.000 [3]: 5.000 <= UL UE thp sample < 10.000 [4]: 10.000 <= UL UE thp sample < 20.000 [5]: 20.000 <= UL UE thp sample < 30.000 [6]: 30.000 <= UL UE thp sample < 60.000 [7]: 60.000 <= UL UE thp sample
The integer part of the GPS time for the most recent occurrence of SFN=0 in the cell.

The period of Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) occasions. Valid periods include 160 ms, 320 ms, 640 ms and 1280 ms.
prsPeriod is used to calculate the prsConfigIndex to avoid PRS sub-frame collisions with SIB1 sub-frames.

Says whether a blind Handover from this cell can be initiated when a UE reports bad coverage, or not. Note that even if the value is True, the eNB will only initiate a blind handover if it finds a suitable cell.
Number of RRC connection reconfiguration attempts (excluding attempt done for mobility purpose).
Successful number of RRC connection reconfiguration attempts (excluding attempt done for mobility purpose).
The number of non-admitted E-RABs at an incoming handover preparation procedure, due to lack of license for RLC UM.
Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) forwarded to target cell at handover for downlink sessions, including packets forwarded during EN-DC setup procedure.
Specifies the start frequency offset for the allocation of resources when the downlink interference management is disabled expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: ulInterferenceManagementActive shall be disabled before this parameter takes effect.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Specifies the amount of frequency resources that is allocated in DL expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Specifies the amount of frequency resources that is allocated in UL expressed as a percentage of the configured bandwidth.

The total number of successful RRC Connection Establishments for Establishment cause Emergency.

Models the manageable characteristics for the cell polygon used for UE positioning. Each polygon corner is described by a latitude and longitude pair. Each polygon corner is represented with one position in the sequence. The other configured polygon corners follow in sequence. There must at least be three corners configured in a polygon when the function is active/used. The points shall be connected in the order that they are given. The last point is connected to the first point.

This parameter holds the resulting prsConfigIndex value. If prsPeriod is used by the operator then prsConfigIndexMapped will be set by the system. If prsConfigIndex is used by the operator then prsConfigIndexMapped will be a copy of the entered value.
The number of RRC Connection Release triggered by CS Fallback for Limited Dual Radio UE LTE/1xRTT.
The total number of added E-RAB Establishment attempts with Privileged Access. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
The total number of successfully added E-RABs with Privileged Access. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
The total number of initial E-RAB Establishment attempts with Privileged Access. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

Specifies the minimum required quality level (RSRQ) in the cell in dB.
Corresponds to Qqualmin in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1. Value 0 means that it is not sent and UE applies in such case the (default) value of negative infinity for Qqualmin.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: The field is mandatory present if the Struct Member threshServingLowQ in SIB3 is used in systemInformationBlockType3.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:

Controls the CFI (Control Format Indicator) used for the control region. cfiMode maps to CFI as described under enumerations. For DL BW of 1400 kHz, values of CFI = 1, 2 and 3 map to 2, 3, and 4 control region symbols respectively. Other BW, CFI maps directly to number of control region symbols.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: pdcchCfiMode cannot equal CFI_STATIC_1 while dlChannelBandwidth = 1400, 3000, or 5000 kHz since there would be insufficient CCEs to transmit a PDCCH for common channel messages such as SIB1 or SI. Certain values of pdcchCfiMode that allow high CFI values may be disallowed when the combination of attributes pdcchCfiMode, dlChannelBandwidth, noOfPucchCqiUsers, and noOfPucchSrUsers require too many corresponding PUCCH HARQ-ARQ resources.

PDF of percentage of CCEs utilized compared with total CCEs available (at the maximum CFI permitted by pdcchCfiMode) each subframe, considering bandwidth and antenna configuration.
PDF ranges: [0]: utilization <= 5% [1]: 5% < utilization <= 10% [2]: 10% < utilization <= 15% [3]: 15% < utilization <= 20% [4]: 20% < utilization <= 25% [5]: 25% < utilization <= 30% [6]: 30% < utilization <= 35% [7]: 35% < utilization <= 40% [8]: 40% < utilization <= 45% [9]: 45% < utilization <= 50% [10]: 50% < utilization <= 55% [11]: 55% < utilization <= 60% [12]: 60% < utilization <= 65% [13]: 65% < utilization <= 70% [14]: 70% < utilization <= 75% [15]: 75% < utilization <= 80% [16]: 80% < utilization <= 85% [17]: 85% < utilization <= 90% [18]: 90% < utilization <= 95% [19]: 95% < utilization <= 100%

Counter of how often the PDCCH has 1 or more CCEs used. To re-normalize pmPdcchCceUtil for subframes containing traffic, use this counter compute and remove idle subframes.

This parameter controls if Contention Free Random Access (CFRA, known as non-contention based random access in 3GPP term) shall be enabled or not. When enabled, a portion of random access preambles should be allocated for CFRA and CFRA can be used for incoming HO and PDCCH ordered uplink re-sync.

The second cell in the pciDetectingCell list corresponds to the second cell in the pciConflictCell list and the first value of pciConflict.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Maximum power boost applied to UE-specific PDCCHs that require more CCEs than the maximum available CCE aggregation level. If UE-specific PDCCHs require equal or less, an automatic power boost algorithm is applied. Attribute pdcchPowerBoostMax does not affect those PDCCHs. If set to 0, there is no PDCCH power boost of the maximum CCE aggregation level. PDCCH coverage is not increased but the feature still optimizes the PDCCH power setting for PDCCHs that require equal or less CCEs than the maximum CCE aggregation level. This still allows for higher PDCCH capacity.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Sets the DL power of the Cell specific Reference Signal (CRS) relatively a reference level defined by the power of the PDSCH type A resource elements. If crsGain is +3dB, the CRS power is 3dB higher than that of a PDSCH type A resource element.
The settings crsGain=4.77db and 6dB are mapped to 3dB. These settings are not supported.
PDSCH type A resource elements are located in symbols that do not contain CRS.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: The crsGain only takes effect if the configured number of antenna ports used in a sector is 2, 4, or 8. In the one port case, crsGain is hardcoded to 0dB.
