ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: A list of network signaling values, where each value corresponds to the frequency band on the same position in additionalFreqBandList. Enables additional spectrum emission requirements according to 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1 when the feature Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is enabled in the cell. The content of this list is based on spectrumEmissionReqMapping. This list will be broadcasted in SIB2 as multiBandInfoList.

A list which maps frequency bands to network signaling values specifying additional spectrum emissions, as described by 3GPP TS 36.101, table 6.2.4-1. A band which is not explicitly mapped to a network signaling value by this list, will use the value NS_01. This list is used to generate the value of additionalSpectrumEmissionValues.

The expected max number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell. Will be used at unlock of the cell to distribute cells to different cores in Digital Units and Baseband Units with a multicore Main Processor. A value of -1 indicates that measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell will be used to control the cell distribution.

Peak number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode measured in the cell. This attribute will be updated during operation of the eNB and used at unlock of the cell to distribute cells to different cores in Digital Units and Baseband Units with a multicore Main Processor. If attribute expectedMaxNoOfUsersInCell is changed from -1 to zero or higher, attribute measuredMaxNoOfUsersInCell will be reset to zero and not used to control the cell distribution.

GINR back-off parameter for PDCCH link adaptation. Applies to all UEs when the feature Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation is disabled. In FDD, if the licenses for both Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation and Carrier Aggregation are enabled, this parameter applies to secondary cell PDCCH for UEs capable of carrier aggregation. In TDD, if the license for Enhanced PDCCH Link Adaptation is enabled, this parameter applies to: - UEs configured with carrier aggregation, and - UEs configured with HARQ-ACK PUCCH format 3 or HARQ-ACK multiplexing.
The number of attempted SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done without using any coverage measurements.
The number of attempted SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done based on coverage measurements. This includes changes of cells due to receiving an A6 report.
The number of successful SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done without using any coverage measurements.
The number of successful SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done based on coverage measurements. This includes changes of cells due to receiving an A6 report.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since L17A. Limited usefulness. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Counts the number of 5-second samples of SCell configuration accumulations included in ROP.
Number of SCell deconfigurations. Has subcounters for specific reasons for SCell deconfiguration.
Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to poor coverage in the SCell.
Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to changing to another SCell.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since L17A. Limited usefulness. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Counts the number of 5-second samples of SCell deconfiguration accumulations included in ROP.
The number of bytes that is assumed to be in the UE buffer when an SR is received through PUCCH.
The number of attempts to start intra LTE intra frequency handover preparation.
The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handover preparations.
The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts.
The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handovers.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations.
The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers.
The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts made by Tune-out UEs
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE intra frequency handovers made by Tune-out UEs.
The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to MBMS Interest.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed due to MBMS Interest.
The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to MBMS Interest.
The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed due to MBMS Interest.
Indicates the upper limit value of cellIndividualOffsetEUtran range that the SON function is allowed to adjust.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Indicates the lower limit value of cellIndividualOffsetEUtran range that the SON function is allowed to adjust.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can stop outgoing HO.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Incremented for each UE in state Out Of Coverage (OOC), for each UL grant designated a new data transmissions (i.e. excluding retransmissions).
Incremented each time a UE enters the state Out Of Coverage (OOC). Trigger for state entry is based on UL measurements indicating poor reception.
Incremented each time a UE exits the state Out Of Coverage (OOC). Trigger for state exit is based on UL measurements indicating good reception.
Incremented at UE release if UE is in state Out Of Coverage (OOC).
The total number of abnormal UE Context Releases by the eNB due to handover execution failure.
The total number of abnormal UE Context releases by the eNB due to that the radio connection with the UE is lost.
The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases per cell by the eNB due to handover execution failure.

The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by the eNB per cell due to that the contact with the UE is lost with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed.
The total number of E-RAB releases by the eNB due to User inactivity.
The total number of E-RAB releases by the eNB per QCI due to User inactivity. Compressed: True.
The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by the eNB per cell due to handover preparation.

The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell due to S1 Interface Down, X2 Interface Down or Transport Resource Unavailable. A precondition is that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed.
The total number of UE context releases by the MME during handover.
The total number of UE context releases by the MME during handover when there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of UE Context Releases by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal.
The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME during handover.
The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME during handover when there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal.
The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME per QCI with a cause regarded as abnormal. Compressed: True.

The number of VoLTE quality measurements that could not be used to determine the VoLTE quality of a VoLTE session (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) due to insufficient statistics. These measurements are excluded when the VoLTE integrity KPI is calculated.
The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of unsatisfactory quality.
The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of satisfactory quality.
Number of CBRA preambles discarded because maximum number of RA Msg3 are already scheduled. CAT-M1 UEs are excluded from this measurement.
The number of CFRA preambles that are discarded because maximum number of RA Msg3 are already scheduled.
Number of CBRA preambles discarded because timing offset of CBRA preamble corresponds to a distance greater than configured cell range.
The number of CFRA preambles that are discarded because timing offset of CFRA preamble corresponds to a distance greater than configured cell range.

The number of times SRVCC to CDMA 1xRtt should have been triggered but the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRtt frequency using Release with Redirect. The counter is stepped if the B2 measurements failed to find a target cell and the target search timer timed out or B2 measurements were not possible.
The number of times the A2 critical report was received from the UE and the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRtt frequency using Release with Redirect.

Number of channel selection resource sets assigned to UEs sharing this PCell within the HARQ bundling window.
PDF ranges: [0]: 1 set [1]: 2 sets ... [11]: 12 sets
Specifies the trigger used in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.
Determines if the OTDOA functionality should be considered in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.
Indicates if release with redirection is allowed in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover.

ARP Priority Level list used in the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover. The first instance in the list is for ARP Priority Level 0, second for 1, and so on. Value "false" means the UE with this bearer is not intended to be moved to other frequency.
How fast the Access Class Barring probability is increased, that is how fast acBarringFactor in SIB2 is decreased when the cell load is increased.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Time period to measure RRC Connection Reject Ratio against threshold lbabThreshRejectRateHigh.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Time period to measure RRC Connection Reject Ratio against threshold lbabThreshRejectRateLow.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: RRC Connection Reject Ratio threshold above which Load-Based Access Barring increases access class barring probability or Progressive Access Barring, or PLMN-Specific Access Barring proceeds to higher priority.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: RRC Connection Reject Ratio threshold below which Load-Based Access Barring decreases access class barring probability or Progressive Access Barring, or PLMN-Specific Access Barring recedes to lower priority.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: How fast the Access Class Barring probability is decreased, that is how fast acBarringFactor in SIB2 is increased when the cell load is decreased.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Minimum time for how often the acBarringFactor in SIB2 can be changed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when Load-Based Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Current barring factor based on LBAB algorithm or PAB algorithm.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect when feature Load-Based Access Barring or feature Progressive Access Barring is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Total time Access Class Barring for Mobile Originating (MO) Signaling was triggered in cell by one of the following features: - Load-Based Access Barring - Progressive Access Barring - Progressive Barring for Special Access Classes - PLMN-Specific Access Barring
PDF ranges: [0]: ac-BarringFactor=p00 [1]: ac-BarringFactor=p05 [2]: ac-BarringFactor=p10 [3]: ac-BarringFactor=p15 [4]: ac-BarringFactor=p20 [5]: ac-BarringFactor=p25 [6]: ac-BarringFactor=p30 [7]: ac-BarringFactor=p40 [8]: ac-BarringFactor=p50 [9]: ac-BarringFactor=p60 [10]: ac-BarringFactor=p70 [11]: ac-BarringFactor=p75 [12]: ac-BarringFactor=p80 [13]: ac-BarringFactor=p85 [14]: ac-BarringFactor=p90 [15]: ac-BarringFactor=p95

Total time Access Class Barring for Mobile Originating (MO) Data was triggered in cell by one of the following features: - Load-Based Access Barring - Progressive Access Barring - Progressive Barring for Special Access Classes - PLMN-Specific Access Barring
PDF ranges: [0]: ac-BarringFactor=p00 [1]: ac-BarringFactor=p05 [2]: ac-BarringFactor=p10 [3]: ac-BarringFactor=p15 [4]: ac-BarringFactor=p20 [5]: ac-BarringFactor=p25 [6]: ac-BarringFactor=p30 [7]: ac-BarringFactor=p40 [8]: ac-BarringFactor=p50 [9]: ac-BarringFactor=p60 [10]: ac-BarringFactor=p70 [11]: ac-BarringFactor=p75 [12]: ac-BarringFactor=p80 [13]: ac-BarringFactor=p85 [14]: ac-BarringFactor=p90 [15]: ac-BarringFactor=p95

The counter shows how long time within the ROP period that the DU or Baseband load control window for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover) has been down regulated from its maximum value due to high MP load.

The counter shows how long time within the ROP period that the cell load control window for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover) has been down regulated from its maximum value due to high procedure latency and/or high drop rate.

Total time Access Class Barring for CSFB was triggered in cell by one of the following features: - Load-Based Access Barring - Progressive Access Barring - Progressive Barring for Special Access Classes - PLMN-Specific Access Barring
PDF ranges: [0]: ac-BarringFactor=p00 [1]: ac-BarringFactor=p05 [2]: ac-BarringFactor=p10 [3]: ac-BarringFactor=p15 [4]: ac-BarringFactor=p20 [5]: ac-BarringFactor=p25 [6]: ac-BarringFactor=p30 [7]: ac-BarringFactor=p40 [8]: ac-BarringFactor=p50 [9]: ac-BarringFactor=p60 [10]: ac-BarringFactor=p70 [11]: ac-BarringFactor=p75 [12]: ac-BarringFactor=p80 [13]: ac-BarringFactor=p85 [14]: ac-BarringFactor=p90 [15]: ac-BarringFactor=p95
Used for selecting whether the PRS transmission must use antenna switching or pre-coder switching.

Used for selecting the different power boosting alternatives for PRS transmissions. If set to 0, a default table based on the number of PBCH antennas and transmission scheme is shown. If set to 1, 2, or 3, it results in a power boosting of 0 dB, 3 dB, or 6 dB respectively.

Used for selecting the length of the PRS muting pattern. Setting the pattern length to 1 results in deactivation of PRS muting. The muting pattern is set to "1111111111111" in this case. Other recommended muting pattern lengths are: 2, 4, 8, and 16 bits.
Used for storing the calculated muting pattern for the cell. This parameter cannot be manually set.
The total number of failed RRC Connection Establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Signaling due to MME overload.
The total number of failed RRC Connection Establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Data due to MME overload.
Indicates the number of times a UE requests a measurement gap for Inter-Frequency OTDOA start or stop and is rejected as no valid license is issued.
Initial preamble power value in dBm, according to 3GPP specification 36.331 and 36.321.

Latency in the scheduler from when an SR is received until grant is issued.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..5] ms [1]: [6..10] ms [2]: [11..20] ms [3]: [21..30] ms [4]: [31..40] ms [5]: [41..50] ms [6]: [51..100] ms [7]: [101..200] ms [8]: [201..500] ms [9]: > 500 ms

Backoff parameter BI value used in RARs (RaMsg2) or BI estimates when the feature Dynamic RA Backoff Indicator is disabled. The BI is included in RARs only when the feature is enabled. BI is calculated independently of the feature state. The corresponding pmRaBackoffDistr bins are incremented.
Time ranges for BI (and BI estimate) below indicate the time that the UEs re-attempt RA within, specified by 3GPP TS 36.321.
PDF ranges: [0]: BI = 0 0 ms [1]: BI = 1 [0..10] ms [2]: BI = 2 [0..20] ms [3]: BI = 3 [0..30] ms [4]: BI = 4 [0..40] ms [5]: BI = 5 [0..60] ms [6]: BI = 6 [0..80] ms [7]: BI = 7 [0..120] ms [8]: BI = 8 [0..160] ms [9]: BI = 9 [0..240] ms [10] BI = 10 [0..320] ms [11]: BI = 11 [0..480] ms [12]: BI = 12 [0..960] ms

Specifies the action performed when a S1AP:E-RAB SETUP REQUEST arrives and both the feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-Frequency Handover is active and the conditions for the bearer request are fulfilled.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This attribute only takes effect when attribute servOrPrioTriggeredIFHo has value 'QCI'.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
The number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover per QCI. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request. Compressed: True.
The number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover per ARP Priority Level. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request. Compressed: True.

Sets the DL power of the PDSCH type B resource elements relatively the PDSCH type A resource elements. Values pdschTypeBGain=(0,1,2,3) define the gains (5/4,1,3/4,1/2) respectively, corresponding to the multi-antenna scenario specified in 3GPP TS 36.213.
Example: If the pdschTypeBGain is 3 (gain=1/2), the power of the PDSCH type B resource elements is a factor 1/ 2 of the power of the PDSCH type A resource elements.
PDSDH type A resource elements are located in symbols that do not contain cell specific reference signals (CRS). PDSCH type B resource elements are located in symbols that contain CRS.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies:
The pdschTypeBGain=0 (gain=5/4) is not allowed if crsGain=1.77,3.0, 4.77,6.0 dB. This combination causes over allocation of DL mean radio power and attribute pdschTypeBGain is set to 1 (gain=1).
The pdschTypeBGain only takes effect if the configured number of antenna ports is 2,4, or 8. In the one port case, the power of resource elements for PDSCH type A and B is equal.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Reports the amount of time in seconds the cell is in MIMO sleep state.
Reports the amount of time in seconds the cell has the opportunity to remain in MIMO sleep state.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Specifies whether or not the function to set the serving frequency as sticky carrier is active in the current cell.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Maximum number of physical resource blocks allowed on PUSCH for each UE.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: This parameter only takes effect if the feature PUCCH Overdimensioning is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Dummy CDMA frequency band in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 information element that can be used to force registration each time the UE moves across LTE and CDMA 1xRTT networks. This can be achieved by setting both this parameter to a dummy band class that is not used in the native CDMA 1xRTT network and by setting the powerUpReg flag to TRUE in SIB-8. The default value of 99 or UNDEFINED_VALUE means the value configured in Cdma2000FreqBand::cdmaBandClass is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 information element which is the same value as the one sent in SIB-8.
Total number of failed RRC Connection Establishments as valid user license limit is exceeded.

Inverse cumulative distribution of number of downlink RLC ARQ retransmissions.
For example, dlMaxRetxThreshold is set to 16. Pegging of bin 0 means RLC PDU is needed to be retransmitted once. Pegging of bin 15 means RLC PDU is needed to be retransmitted 16 times (dlMaxRetxThreshold). Pegging of bin 16 means RLC PDU is not successfully delivered after dlMaxRetxThreshold is reached (RLF).
Note that if dlMaxRetxThreshold > 16, then bin 16 is no longer counting only RLF but also aggregating 17 or more retransmissions for same SN.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of downlink RLC PDUs which need one retransmission for same SN. [1]: Number of downlink RLC PDUs which need two retransmissions for same SN. ... [16]: Number of downlink RLC PDUs which need 17 or more retransmissions for same SN.
The number of sending downlink AM PDU retransmissions due to the poll retransmit timer expiry.
This counter counts the number of receiving uplink AM PDU retransmissions due to the poll retransmit timer expiry.
The number of Scheduled Entities (SEs) in the uplink per cell, including TTI bundling grants and nonAdaptive re-transmissions. If divided with the number of TTIs, SE/TTI average can be obtained.

The number of complete HARQ failures. When a HARQ transmission has reached maximum number of retransmissions, it will not be retransmitted again and is regarded as a scheduling activity complete HARQ failure.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since L17A. Replaced by pmPdcpPktLostUlMissingPdus2Qci. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of lost packets in UL due to any of the following causes, differentiated per QCI. Causes are either RLC re-assembly failure, HARQ failure or UE PDCP discarded packets due to outdated PDUs.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since L17A. Replaced by pmPdcpPktLostUlRohcFail2Qci. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: The number of lost packets in UL due to RoHC decompression failures, differentiated per QCI.
The number of lost packets in UL due to PDCP capacity limitations.
The number of times the UE switches on TTI bundling mode.
The number of times the UE switches off TTI bundling mode.
The number of times the UE switches on or off TTI bundling mode and fails due to time out.
Number of RRC Connection Re-establishment attempts differentiated for each QCI. Counter is only stepped if Context Fetch procedure is successful. Compressed: True
The number of successful RRC Connection Reestablishments differentiated per QCI. Compressed: True
The total number of failed S1 signaling connection establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Signaling due to MME overload.
The total number of transmitted unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions.
The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions. The grants are transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions. The grants are transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell, and that have no bearer mapped to a QCI with VoIP serviceType.

Delay distribution between reception of random access message 3 and successful transmission of random access message 4. Only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection setup, or an RRC connection re-establishment message.
PDF ranges: [0]: =< 8 ms [1]: ]8..16] ms [2]: ]16..24] ms [3]: ]24..32] ms [4]: ]32..40] ms [5]: ]40..48] ms [6]: ]48..56] ms [7]: ]56..64] ms [8]: > 64 ms

The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has not expired. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection setup or an RRC connection re-establishment message.

The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has expired. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection setup or an RRC connection re-establishment message.

Delay distribution between reception of random access message 3 and successful transmission of random access message 4. Only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and no RRC message or a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection reject or an RRC connection re-establishment reject message.

The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has not expired. The fraction of non-qualified UEs at UE selection for throughput aware load balancing. In case throughput aware UE selection is enabled, this parameter sets a target size for the fraction of UE to be disqualified for load balancing due to insufficient relative gain when moving UE from source to target cell. Special value 0 means that the throughput aware UE selection for this cell is disabled.

The minimum threshold for the relative gain at throughput aware load balancing. A negative value may allow for some throughput loss for the individual UE, if the load balancing criteria requires so. Higher values may increase the fraction of non-qualified UEs at UE selection for throughput aware load balancing and may cause the load balancing to stall. Special value -100 means the lower boundary for the threshold is disabled.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Controls the LCGs that are included in pmMacUeThpVolUl, pmMacUeThpTimeUl, and pmMacUeThpUlDistr. To include the n:th LCG, set includeLcgInMacUeThp[n]=true.

The transfer time used for UL Cell throughput. It consists of the number of ms in which there is need for DRB transmission for at least one UE in the cell. The transfer time includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions

Transfer time used for UL UE throughput. Comprised of the number of ms in which there is need for transmission on at least one of the LCGs specified in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::includeLcgInMacUeThp. Transfer time includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.

Volume used for UL LCG throughput. Consists of the MAC SDU volume received for each LCG. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transmitted volume over all carriers is registered on PCell.

Transfer time used for UL LCG throughput. Consists of the number of ms in which there is need for transmission for the LCG. Includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.

Volume used for UL UE throughput. Consists of the MAC SDU volume received for the LCGs specified in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::includeLcgInMacUeThp. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transmitted volume over all carriers is registered on PCell.

Total number of successful RRC Connection Reconfigurations. Used to facilitate CA.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction of carrier aggregation UE.

The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers of carrier aggregation UE that has been transferred (acknowledged by the carrier aggregation UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied.

The effective DL transport time of carrier aggregation UE comprises those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer. This is used for PDCP timebase.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The effective DL transport time, comprising those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer, is registered on PCell.

The UL DRB volume used for UL carrier aggregation UE throughput. Comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in first 4 data receptions of UL buffer transfer and TTI emptying UL buffer.

The UL volume transfer time used for UL carrier aggregation UE Throughput. Comprised of time periods from reception of 5th MAC SDU data in UL buffer transfer on Uu until buffer is empty. TTI emptying buffer is excluded.

Distribution of the DL UE throughput. One DL UE throughput sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers per UE, that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction, with a time interval applicable to the volume measurement. Bandwidth-reduced UEs are excluded from this measurement.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

Specifies if outgoing uplink-triggered mobility actions are enabled or disabled in the cell. Used when Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is enabled. The parameter has effect if Mobility Control in Poor Coverage is enabled and mobCtrlAtPoorCovActive is set to true in the cell.
Normally this counter is not used, it can however sometimes be temporarily used for very late additions in a release. If so, for description see Network Impact Report in the CPI.
PDCCH DCI format 1A is used for SRB to increase transmission success rate and to minimize interruption time.
PDCCH DCI format 1A to increase MOS for QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT in high interference or high path loss scenarios.
PDCCH DCI format 1A for first retransmission due to DTX of SRB and serviceType VoIP or PTT.
New unicast DL assignments transmitted during DRX onDuration.
New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration.
New unicast DL assignments sent during DRX onDuration and confirmed by corresponding HARQ ACK/NACK.
New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration and confirmed by corresponding PUSCH transmission.
New unicast DL assignments transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs that have bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. DL assignments are excluded if this cell is SCell for those UEs.
New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs that have bearer mapped to QCI with service type VoIP.

New unicast DL assignments that are transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs with bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. Reception must be confirmed by corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block. DL assignments are excluded if this cell is SCell for those UEs.
New unicast UL grants that are transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs with bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. Reception must be confirmed by corresponding PUSCH transmission.

Relative priority in initial SCell selection for cells that can be configured with UL Carrier Aggregation. Applicable where several SCells are initially configured simultaneously. Lowest value has highest priority.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Applicable when 3CC Carrier aggregation Extension Feature (FAJ 121 3084) is enabled and sCellSelectionMode is equal to UN_ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION or ACK_SIMULTANEOUS_SCELL_SELECTION.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: List of additional frequency bands the cell belongs to. Primary frequency band, EARFCN value of the cell, is not included. Secondary cell evaluation is done according to list order, and/or the list is broadcasted in SIB1. Highest priority band is position 0 in the list.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: List only contains frequency bands from additionalFreqBandList. Only applicable if ENodeBFunction::useBandPrioritiesInSCellEval or EUtranCellFDD/TDD::mfbiFreqBandIndPrio is enabled.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Defines how many dB higher than the original SR detection threshold can be used as high SR detection threshold. Used together with srProcessingLevel to reduce false SR detection.
Defines how many SRs eNodeB must receive in a row in order to process it. Used together with srDetectHighThres to reduce false SR detection.
Controls adaptive CFI to avoid using CFI=1 or CFI=1,2, when scheduling UEs that are in handover. The highest CFI value in available CFI values determined by pdcchCfiMode is not prohibited.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Applicable only when attribute pdcchCfiMode is set to CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_2 or CFI_AUTO_MAXIMUM_3.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Controls if link adaptation function allocates largest possible resource to last scheduled UE in the DL. Used to improve UE decoding success rate with reduced code rate.

Maximum number of physical resource blocks (PRBs) allowed on PDSCH for each UE. Note: If the set value is larger than the system bandwidth, then the system bandwidth value will be used instead. For PDSCH resource allocation type 0, the actual maximum number of PRBs that is allocated will be a multiple of RBGs (Resource Block Groups) that is nearest to the set value but without exceeding it.
Total number of RRC Connection Releases that are sent by the eNodeB without expecting any acknowledgement.
Total number of successfully established PFT sessions.

SI validity timer. The timer is set to 3h or 24h.
Min received RSRP level in E-UTRA frequency for cell reselection for UE in enhanced coverage mode. Corresponds to parameter Qrxlevmin_CE in 3GPP TS 36.304. This attribute is broadcast in SIB1-BR.

Min quality level (RSRQ) in cell for UE in enhanced coverage mode.
Corresponds to Qqualmin_CE in TS 36.304, sent in SIB1-BR. If 0, it is not sent and UE applies default value of negative infinity for Qqualmin_CE.
Enables Dynamic uplink resource allocation on cell level.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only relevant if license UlDynamicResourceAllocation is present and feature is active.

Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of abnormal E-RAB releases by MME.

Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

Number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by eNB. Counter is stepped if data was present in UL or DL buffers.

Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME within this cell.

Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME within this cell. Counter is stepped if data was present in UL or DL buffers.

UL transmission time used for UL DRB Throughput. It is comprised of time periods from when the 5th data transmission is received on Uu until the second last data transmission is received.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

Aggregated DL Latency for measurement period. Effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering buffer until the first data has been transmitted to UE.
When CA is used, DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of DRB packets for DL Latency measurements.
When CA is used, DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

DL MAC DRB latency time.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Specifies if SINR-based UL power control can be used or not. If enabled, SNR-based closed-loop power control and SINR-based closed-loop power control can be adaptively selected.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Attribute only has effect if feature Differential Uplink Power Control is activated.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: SINR target value for SINR-based UL closed-loop power control.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: SINR target only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Threshold value for measured noise plus interference level. If measured noise plus interference is higher than interferenceThresholdSinrClpc, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Threshold of UL transmission power per PRB. If averaged UL transmission power measurement per PRB is lower than ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc over a set percentage of UL bandwidth, then SINR-based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Threshold only has effect if attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc is true.

Threshold number of SCells configured by Carrier Aggregation (CA) users with this cell as PCell. When number of SCells configured for UEs connected in this PCell is higher than caPrioThreshold, following rules apply: - For Configurable SCell Priority, all frequency carriers configured for CA are assumed to have equal priority regardless of configured values. - For Global SCell Evaluation, all SCell relations from PCell are handled equally regardless of threshold for number of SCell UEs.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only applicable when Configurable SCell Priority is active with following apply: - dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to PRIORITIZED. - dynamicSCellSelectionMethod is set to GLOBAL_EVALUATION.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:takesEffect: New connection or next SCell configuration.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs that do not have a secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

Initial value for PDCCH outer loop adjustment for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

Initial value for primary cell PDCCH outer loop adjustment in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have a bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have a bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.
PDCCH outer loop up step size for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

PDCCH outer loop up step size for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

PDCCH target error rate for UEs that do not have any secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.
PDCCH target error rate for UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter applies only to UEs which are configured with HARQ-ACK bundling.

PDCCH target error rate for primary cells in case of carrier aggregation. This applies to UEs that have at least one secondary cell configured and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP or PTT. In TDD, this parameter is not used.

The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. The DL assignments are excluded if this cell is a secondary cell for those UEs.

The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block. The DL assignments are excluded if this cell is a secondary cell for those UEs.

The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is unknown. The DL assignments are excluded if this cell is a secondary cell for those UEs.
The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

The total number of unicast UL grants that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.
The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as a secondary cell.

The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs using this cell as a secondary cell, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block.
The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs using this cell as a secondary cell, for which the reception is unknown.
The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block.

The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is unknown.
The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

Enable automatic configuration of tReorderingDl and tReorderingUl. Configuration is based on HARQ-interval together with an offset defined by harqOffsetDl/harqOffsetUl.tReordering >= 'Max number of HARQ' * HARQ-interval + harqOffset, where closest higher or equal allowed value is used.
This configuration is only applied to UM bearers. AM bearers will still use tReorderingUl and tReorderingDl from QciProfilePredefined or QciProfileOperatorDefined.
Offset used when tReorderingDl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingDl = 'Max number of HARQ for DL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetDl.
Offset used when tReorderingUl is calculated by automatic configuration. tReorderingUl = 'Max number of HARQ for UL' * HARQ-interval + harqOffsetUl.
Enables function to automatically adapt t-PollretransmitTimer to the time it takes to complete HARQ procedure + harqOffset (UL and DL).
Enable/disable service-specific HARQ on cell level. Function must have valid license.
Number of failed cell sleep attempts due to lack of UE capability for the coverage frequency. Used when cell sleep is attempted every minute for daily time interval.

Total number of PRB pairs used in DL for HARQ retransmissions for CAT-M1 UEs.

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) for which no part has been transmitted in DL that are discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) for which at least a part has been transmitted in DL but not ACKed, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, due to reasons other than handover. Only applicable to DRB packets.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in downlink due to handover and reestablishment procedures, including procedures for EN-DC setup.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in the downlink due to handover and reestablishment procedures is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received by eNB in PDCP in DL.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received by eNB in PDCP in DL is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) forwarded to target cell at handover for DL sessions, including handover during EN-DC setup procedure.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters LCG, ARP, QCI, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received in the UL.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) lost in the UL.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters LCG and ENDC are not applicable.
Accumulated sum of DL PRB capacity usage for Cat-M1 UEs. Increasing when cell is active, even when there are no UEs connected, due to traffic on BCCH and PCCH.
Number of measured samples of DL PRB capacity usage for Cat-M1 UEs.

Peak value of DL PRB capacity usage for Cat-M1 UEs. Value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of PRB use for each ms (throughout frame), during a sample period shorter than ROP.
Accumulated sum of UL PRB capacity usage for Cat-M1 UEs.
Number of measured samples of UL PRB capacity usage for Cat-M1 UEs.

Peak value of UL PRB capacity usage for Cat-M1 UEs. Value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of PRB use for each ms (throughout frame), during a sample period shorter than ROP.

Total volume (PDCP SDU) on data radio bearers that has been received in the UL direction and transmitted over the GTP-U.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Accumulated active session time for all UEs in a cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters LCG, ARP, QCI, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

Counters shows the accumulated active session time for all DRBs in a cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of service seconds aggregated for UEs in a cell. A UE is said to be in service if any of its associated DRBs are.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters LCG, ARP, QCI, and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of service seconds aggregated for DRBs in a cell. A DRB is said to be in service from the first data on a DRB (UL or DL) until the last on the DRB is sent/received.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 17.Q3. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Total transferred data on MAC level in UL. This counter can include padding bits. Only applies to UEs that use this cell as their PCell or SCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters LCG, ARP, QCI, and ENDC are not applicable.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 17.Q3. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Total volume successfully transferred on MAC level in the DL. This counter can include padding bits.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters LCG, ARP, QCI, and ENDC are not applicable.

Number of S1AP paging messages discarded and not broadcasted in this cell for bandwidth-reduced UEs. Subset of pmPagReceivedCe. Both non-prioritized, prioritized S1AP paging messages and eDRX pagings are included.
PDF ranges: [0]: Discarded paging messages [1]: Not used [2]: Not used [3]: Not used

Number of S1AP paging messages routed to this cell for bandwidth-reduced UEs. Both non-prioritized, prioritized S1AP paging and eDRX paging messages are included.
PDF ranges: [0]: Received paging messages [1]: Not used [2]: Not used [3]: Not used

Number of bandwidth reduced UEs considered active in the DL direction, per PRACH Coverage Enhancement (CE) level.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

Number of bandwidth reduced UEs considered active in the UL direction, per PRACH Coverage Enhancement (CE) level.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

Stepped at reception of S1 message UE context release command with internal cause codes considered abnormal (Radio connection with UE is lost; Handover failure for the UE; UE pre-emption) when the RBS initiated the release. It can also be stepped at transmission of UE context release request or reset message by the RBS, or when a cell owned by that RBS is disabled (and that leads to internal RBS UE context release).
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP, LCG, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

Total number of UE context releases initiated by the MME excluding successful handover. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP, LCG, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

Total number of UE context releases initiated by the MME excluding successful handover and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP, LCG, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

Total number of normal UE context releases triggered by RBS. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP, LCG, ENDC, PCI, and PVI are not applicable.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by pmActiveUeDlCe0Max, pmActiveUeDlCe1Max, pmActiveUeDlCe2Max and pmActiveUeDlCe3Max. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Peak number of bandwidth reduced UEs considered active in the DL direction, per PRACH Coverage Enhancement (CE) level. A UE is considered active if it has designated data in its dedicated buffer in the eNB. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 17.Q3. Replaced by pmActiveUeUlCe0Max, pmActiveUeUlCe1Max, pmActiveUeUlCe2Max and pmActiveUeUlCe3Max. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Peak number of bandwidth reduced UEs considered active in the UL direction, per PRACH Coverage Enhancement (CE) level. A UE is considered active if it has data in its buffer. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3
SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values go higher, more candidates are selected for Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP, but more user measurements are triggered. This impacts MP load and transport load over X2.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrHys.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Hysteresis of SINR threshold for inter-eNodeB UL CoMP user selection.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: If changed, system performance can be affected. As values get bigger, gaps for triggering Inter-eNodeB Uplink CoMP user switching get bigger.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Must be used together with interEnbUlCompUserSelSinrThr.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Threshold for % of PRBs with "UL Tx power per PRB >= ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc" during measSinrClpcPeriod. Below threshold means low cell power load and then SINR based UL closed-loop power control can be considered.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Attribute enableSinrUplinkClpc must be true.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Number of periods that closed-loop power control in uplink select P-zero based algorithm in the cell.
Number of periods that closed-loop power control in uplink select SINR based algorithm in the cell.

Distribution of Ul Tx PSD load level. % of PRBs with "UL Tx power Per PRB >= ulPsdLoadThresholdSinrClpc". Bin counter stepped every measSinrClpcPeriod.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..10]% [1]: ]10..20]% [2]: ]20..30]% [3]: ]30..40]% [4]: ]40..50]% [5]: ]50..60]% [6]: ]60..70]% [7]: ]70..80]% [8]: ]80..90]% [9]: ]90..100]%

The number of failed RRC Connection Establishments due to the DU or Baseband connection intensity control from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

The number of rejected RRC Connection setup triggered by the MP Overload state from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

Number of failed RRC Connection Establishments due to high DU or Baseband SW component load from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

The number of failed RRC Connection Establishments in the cell due to Procedure Latency Supervision from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

The number of failed RRC Connection Establishments due to cell connection intensity control regulated by Dynamic Load Control from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

The number of failed RRC Connection Establishments due to static cell connection intensity control from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

Total number of non-privileged RRC connection requests rejected by UE Admission Control from bandwidth-reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

Number of failed RRC Connection Establishments in the cell due to high SW component load on cell from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

Total number of non-privileged RRC connection re-establishment requests rejected by Dynamic UE Admission Control from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3

The number of RRC Connection Reestablishment attempts from bandwidth reduced UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1 [2]: CE level 2 [3]: CE level 3
Shows the subframes that are reserved for MBSFN in DL.
Whether or not UL scheduler is enabled to force allocation of PRBs to Data-Aware, UL-Scheduling UEs last.
Number of data-aware UL-scheduling UEs that can be improved at allocation of PDCCH and PUSCH.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Whether or not UL-scheduler is enabled that uses adaptive re-transmission more frequently for data-aware UL-scheduling UEs, to reduce fragments in UL spectrum.
Threshold used to help identify data-aware UL scheduling UEs. If BSR >= bsrThreshold, UE becomes candidate UE for UL improvement.

Length of time eNodeB rejects traffic requests from non-privileged UEs when detecting high procedure latency. Used in Procedure Latency Supervision. Privileged traffic, such as High Priority Access (HPA) and Emergency, is never rejected due to high procedure latency conditions.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:lifeCycleDesc: Since 17.Q3. Has no functional behavior. Planned to be removed.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Whether or not SCell selection for high power UE that is not capable of CA simultaneously is enabled.

Number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) successfully transmitted (RLC acknowledged by UE) in the downlink.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) successfully transmitted (RLC acknowledged by UE) in the downlink is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Peak number of UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 0.

Peak number of UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 3.

Peak number of UEs that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 0 and that are considered active in the DL direction. A UE is considered active if it has designated data in its dedicated buffer in the eNB. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

Peak number of UEs that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 1 and that are considered active in the DL direction. A UE is considered active if it has designated data in its dedicated buffer in the eNB. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

Peak number of UEs that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 2 and that are considered active in the DL direction. Peak number of UEs that connected on bandwidth reduced PRACH using Coverage Enhancement level 0 and that are considered active in the UL direction. A UE is considered active if it has data in its buffer. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

Filtered volume (PDCP SDU) on DRB that was transmitted in DL direction in PDCP layer for UEs.

Threshold used in restrict SE number that enhanced adaptive Retransmission candidates, if there are too many non-adaptive retransmission candidates, only "noOfEnhAdptReTxCand" numbers SE can be the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue. Maximum number of SEs added to the enhanced adaptive retransmission queue as candidates. If set to -1, number of candidates is automatically decided by eNodeB. If set to 0, no UEs added to queue and thus feature has no effect.

The uplink volume transfer time used for uplink UE throughput. It comprises of time periods up to the fourth MAC SDU data reception of an uplink buffer transfer on Uu until the buffer is emptied, including the TTI emptying the buffer.

The uplink DRB volume used for UL UE throughput. It comprises of the MAC SDU volume received on Uu corresponding to the volume received up to the fourth data reception of an uplink buffer transfer and the TTI emptying the uplink buffer.
Enables PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Value of threshold to enable the PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling. PUSCH 100 PRBs scheduling is triggered when the number of UE in RRC_CONNECTED mode in the cell is less than or equal to ns05FullBandUsersInCellThres.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and - attribute ns05FullBandSchedEnabled in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is true.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Controls if the low band can be allocated to NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_PROHIBIT', the low band cannot be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ALWAYS_AVAILABLE', the low band can always be allocated to the NS_05 UEs. When ns05LowBandSchedMode is configured to 'ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION', the low band can only be allocated to the NS_05 UEs which are detected as not in repeater zone.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Value of threshold to detect if the NS_05 UE is in repeater zone. If the NS_05 UE's pathloss measured on low band is bigger than or equal to the value of other band plus ns05PathlossOffsetThres, the NS_05 UE is detected as in repeater zone.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if: - license for NS 05 Additional Maximum Power Reduction Support is present and the feature is active, and - attribute networkSignallingValue in MOC EUtranCellFDD/TDD is NS_05, and - attribute ns05LowBandSchedMode is ADAPTIVE_AVAILABLE_BY_REPEATER_DETECTION.

Reference to a list of MeasCellGroup MOs for grouping on UE basis. Referenced Mos include measurements on differentiated UEs into a measurement group.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: MeasCellGroup with 0 groupId can not be referred. MeasCellGroup with empty spidList and empty plmnList can not be referred. MeasCellGroup with non-empty plmnList and MeasCellGroup having non null spidList can not be referred together. Duplication of plmn or spid within referred MeasCellGroups is not allowed.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Controls which DL subframes are unavailable for Cat-M DL due to MBMS operation. Fewer unavailable subframes optimize Cat-M1 DL max throughput, but change of unavailable subframes can cause Cat-M1 connection drops and temporary difficulties to page certain UEs. Avoided by less dynamic setting (lower value). 0: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to MbsfnArea::commonSFAllocList and MbsfnArea::mbsfnAreaCellRelation. 1: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to MbsfnArea::commonSFAllocList and MbsfnArea::mbsfnAreaCellRelation if any MBSFN service is active in the cell, otherwise no unavailable subframes due to MBMS. 2: Unavailable subframes due to MBMS set according to subframes blocked by active MBSFN services.

Shows valid subframes for DL BR transmissions, indicated by broadcasted SIB1-BR. 1: Corresponding subframe is valid DL BR subframe. 0: Corresponding subframe not valid DL BR subframe. First element in the list corresponds to radio frames satisfying SFN mod 4 = 0, the next to radio frames satisfying SFN mod 4 = 1 and so on. Each least significant bit represents subframe #0 of the corresponding SFN. If SIB1-BR not broadcasted (Cat-M not supported in cell), list is empty.

Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases per cell, initiated by RBS due to UE preemption with precondition of successfully completed Initial Context Establishment procedure. Stepped regardless of UL/DL buffer data loss.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.

Total numer of abnormal GBR E-RAB releases per cell, initiated by RBS due to UE preemption with precondition of successfully completed Initial Context Establishment procedure. Stepped regardless of UL/DL buffer data loss.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG and ENDC are not applicable.
Number of times corresponding Sum counter accumulates new samples. Associated ACC pmCounter is pmFlexRrcConnSum.

Sum of sample values recorded for "number of UEs in RRC_CONNECTED mode".
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters PLMN and SPID are applicable.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can affect traffic.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc:
Changes priorities of bands for Multiple Frequency Band Indicators.
If true: Cell broadcasts freqBandIndicatorPriority in SIB1, and FreqBandIndicatorPriority=broadcasted is sent over X2 interface to neighbor eNB. Prioritized additional frequency band list (prioAdditionalFreqBandList) is broadcasted in SIB1 and is also used for handovers (including S1 and X2 handovers) instead of additionalFreqBandList. If UE indicates freqBandPriorityAdjustment capability (support of freqBandIndicatorPriority), primary band has the lowest priority, otherwise primary band has the highest priority. mfbiFreqBandIndPrio is not used for handovers between Ericsson eNBs if ENodeBFunction::caAwareMfbiIntraCellHo = true.
If false: Cell doesn't broadcast freqBandIndicatorPriority in SIB1, and FreqBandIndicatorPriority=not-broadcasted is sent over X2 interface to neighbor eNB. additionalFreqBandList is broadcasted in SIB1 and is also used for handovers (including S1 and X2 handovers). Primary band always has the highest priority.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns2:disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause loss of traffic. X2 handover and Connection Setup for MFBI capable UE can fail during a few seconds, leading to dropped calls.
ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns3:dependencies: Only takes effect if Multiple Frequency Band Indicators is active.

ns2:primaryTypeAttribute.ns1:desc: Temporary attributes are intended as temporary solutions. Their usage can vary depending on the installed software. It is strongly recommended to only set the attributes that correspond to a desired functionality and leave all other temporary attributes set to default value. Information in the descriptions about what attributes are in use can be overridden by the information in CPI documents. Note that a later release can use another attribute to control functionality previously provided by a temporary attribute, or can remove functionality altogether. In these cases, the change is documented in the NIR.

ns2:primaryTypeAction.ns1:desc:
Changes the frequency of the cell. The attribute earfcndl is changed. This MO action includes the following steps:
- An instance of EUtranFrequency with correct frequency is created (if not already existing).
- For neigbouring cells with existing cell relations to the cell, create new EUtranFreqRelation instances (if not already existing) and new EUtranCellRelation instances (with the same attribute values as the existing EUtranFreqRelation and EUtranCellRelation MOs).
- For the changed cell an instance of EUtranFreqRelation with reference to the correct instance of EUtranFrequency is created, if not already existing (with the same attribute values as the existing EUtranFreqRelation MO).
Note that changing frequency of a EUtranCellFDD will imply that all other eNBs that have this cell configured as an ExternaEUtranCellFDD will be updated with the new frequency. This means that new EUtranFreqRelation and corresponding EUtranFrequency MOs might be created.

ns2:parameter.ns1:desc: The new DL frequency for this cell.

ns2:primaryTypeAction.ns2:disturbances: Changes may affect traffic. The cell will be automatic locked/unlocked if needed.
